}}'''Veliki Novgorod''' ([[lingaz rus|rus]]: Великий Новгород), ënghe mé cunesciuda coche '''Novgorod''' (Новгород), ie na [[zità]] de la [[Ruscia]] y la [[capitela]] dl [[oblast de Novgorod]] tl [[Raion Federel de Nord-vest]]. Tl 2021 ovela na populazion de {{formatnum:225019}}<ref name="2015Est">Statistiches Stateles de la Federazion Russa - Raion Oblast. [http://kemerovostat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/kemerovostat/resources/3ff9a5804351eba5bc0dfd74665da2b8/%D0%9A%D0%9E.htm Численность населения Кемеровской области на начало года] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171022175241/http://kemerovostat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/kemerovostat/resources/3ff9a5804351eba5bc0dfd74665da2b8/%D0%9A%D0%9E.htm |date=October 22, 2017 }} per rus</ref>. La zità ie te la [[zona d’orar]] [[UTC+3]]. La parola ''veliki'' per [[lingaz rus|rus]] uel di "grant", perchël ie l inuem de la zità l ''gran Novgorod''. Chësc ie per deferenzië la zità da [[Nijni Novgorod]] (literalmënter l ''Novgorod bas'', ajache plu injù sce n ti va do ala [[Volga]]), che ie aldidancuei majera y scebën che la ie ënghe vedla, ne ala nia la storia longia y mpurtanta de Novgorod.

== Storia ==
Novgorod ie una de la ziteies plu vedles de la Ruscia, la fova stata documenteda bel tl 9ejim secul<ref>''The Archaeology of Novgorod,'' by [[Valentin L. Yanin]], in ''Ancient Cities, Special Issue,'' (Scientific American), pp.&nbsp;120–127, c.&nbsp;1994. Covers, History, Kremlin of Novgorod, Novgorod Museum of History, preservation dynamics of the soils, and the production of [[Birch bark document]]s.</ref> Dal 1992 incà fej Novgorod pert de la [[arpejon mondiela UNESCO]].

Tl 1136 ova scumencià la [[Republica de Novgorod]], che fova deventeda l cumëmber plu a est de la [[Lia de la Hanse]] y fluriva dal 12ejim al 15ejim secul. Tl 1478 fova la Republica de Novgorod stata desdruda y tëuta ite dal [[Ducat de Moscau]]. 

